<p><b>Divisualise!</b> is an extensible, interactive divide-and-conquer algorithm visualiser created by <a href="https://armandcoretchi.com" target="_blank" class="text-blue-400 underline">Armand Coretchi</a>.</p>
<br>
<p>Exposing a simple API, Divisualise! is designed to be easily extensible by teachers and advanced students who wish to create their own visualisations. Define an algorithm and implement its naive recursive implementation - get input handling, presentation, and dynamic programming for free!</p>
<br>
<p>Divisualise! is built with SvelteKit, TypeScript and Tailwind CSS. The source code is available on <a class="text-blue-400 underline" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/acoretchi/divisualise">GitHub</a> under the GPL-3.0 license. Contributions in the form of algorithm implementations or other improvements are welcome and encouraged!</p>
